# Tooltip & Window Management — Critical Invariants

## Window Architecture

The meter runs as a **transparent, frameless, always-on-top Electron BrowserWindow**. Transparent pixels are click-through to EQ. The window is sized to fit only the meter panel; tooltips require temporarily expanding it.

## Tooltip Expansion (index.ts)

When a user hovers a bar, the renderer asks the main process to expand the window so the tooltip has room to render outside the meter panel.

**Rules:**
- Store `baseBounds` BEFORE expanding so collapse restores the exact original size/position
- Expand downward to the display `workArea` bottom, clamped to screen edges
- On collapse, restore from `baseBounds` (never subtract a fixed constant)
- `collapseTooltipExpansion()` is called from multiple places: collapse IPC, `saveCurrentLayout()`, `repositionMeterToEQ()`, `start-resize`. All must work correctly.

## Tooltip Rendering (DamageMeter.tsx)

The tooltip is `position: fixed` rendered as a sibling of the meter panel div (inside a React Fragment), NOT inside the overflow-hidden meter panel.

**Rules:**
- Never use `maxHeight` or `overflowY: 'auto'` on the tooltip — this clips content and scroll conflicts with EQ
- Direction logic: prefer whichever side (above/below bar) has more space
- The tooltip uses `pointerEvents: 'none'`

## Meter Stability (App.tsx)

The App wraps DamageMeter in a div with `height: meterH`. This keeps the meter visually stable during tooltip expansion.

**Rules:**
- `meterH` updates ONLY during user-initiated resize (`resizing.current === true`)
- Tooltip-triggered window resizes call `forceRender()` instead, which re-renders without changing meter height
- Never update `meterH` from tooltip expand/collapse events

## Drag (App.tsx + index.ts)

Drag uses `mousedown` on title bar → track delta → send `move-window` IPC with `(screenX - clientX, screenY - clientY)` as absolute position.

**Rules:**
- `dragAnchor` stores initial `clientX/clientY` (NOT screenX/screenY)
- `move-window` handler calls `mainWindow.setPosition(x, y)` with absolute coords
- Must work in all directions (up, down, left, right)

## Resize (App.tsx + index.ts)

Resize uses the bottom-right grip → `start-resize` IPC → main process polls cursor position at 16ms intervals.

**Rules:**
- `resizeStart` stores initial cursor screenX/screenY and initial window w/h
- New size = `initial + (currentCursor - initialCursor)`, clamped to minimums (200x100)
- `collapseTooltipExpansion()` is called before starting resize
- `stopResizePolling()` saves layout to disk
- `resizing.current` flag distinguishes user resize from tooltip resize in the renderer
